The paper deals with question answering using neural networks, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel neural network architecture, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper involves sequential processing of information, which is a common theme in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval and knowledge representation, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
